column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Partly sunny- light W breeze.  Bald eagle over S half.  Rain this day (very early a.m.) .  More expected. k.a.p.
Mostly sunny- light south-southwest breeze- possible osprey snatched fish from south half of lake- with bald eagle soaring overhead osprey.  K.a.p.
Sunny- light SW breeze.  Looks like a bit more algae suspended in water.  A bit more than previously.  Bald eagle over S half landed in white pine on the point.  Nights about 32 degrees F.  K.a.p.
Partly cloudy- light WNW breeze-switching to southwest.  Two deer on W shore at 3: 40 p.m.  Blue heron standing at S shore-n of pioneer creek at 3: 50 p.m.  Appears that lake has "turned over".  Kap
Partly cloudy- south-southwest breeze.  No white caps- increasing clouds and wind.  Gulls were the wildlife today.  Snow on 9-22-95. kap
Partly sunny- high cirrus.  South-southwest breeze (no white caps) - clouds increasing.  Bald eagle over north half.  Two loons: one in north half- the other a short distance north of island. kap
Partly cloudy- light west-southwest breeze- cumulus and cirrus clouds.  Light rain yesterday.  Two gulls in area of rock.  Heron at public landing shore.  Kap
Partly cloudy- SW breeze- cirrus clouds.  Numerous gulls sheltering in island.  Kap
Partly sunny- light NW breeze.  Cumulo-cirrus clouds.  There were a few gulls.  Kap
Partly sunny- cirrostratus clouds.  South-southwest breeze (no white caps) .  Water appeared nearly clear at 1'.  This will be my last card for 1995.  See you in spring.  Kap
Partly sunny- SW breeze. no whitecaps in lulls. bald eagle over point. 32 ducks on N side of point.
With this reading participated in the great 1996 secchi dip-in. Sunny- light N breeze. No whitecaps. Bald eagle over southern part of lake.
Sunny- light W breeze. occasional rain on 7/9 until early afternoon. gulls heard but not seen.
Partly cloudy- breeze out of the west (no whitecaps) . rained most of last week- rained on 7-15 last- more expected. visited by lone loon (25' from boat) . cute!

Partly cloudy (cirrus) - light south-southeast breeze (no whitecaps) . slightly more suspended particles than previously. two bald eagles over north side of lake. hawk went fishing. rain expected on 7-22. last rain on 7-18.

Partly sunny- cumulus. NNW breeze (no whitecaps) . occasional rain from 7/22-7/24. suspended particles in water same as on 7/21. lone bald eagle caught lunch near point. perched on island white pine later.
Sunny- light NW breeze (no whitecaps) . rainy period from 7/27-7/31. water appeared slightly more greenish than last. 2 bald eagles (one over point- other over lake's north) . unseen loon heard.

Partly sunny- light NNW breeze (no whitecaps) . lake in midst of algal bloom. rain on 8/5 and 8/7. loon bobbing on N side of lake- 5 ducks at mouth of pioneer creek. heron seen .75 mile down pioneer creek.

Rain on 8/12 to 8/15 (periodic) . partly cloudy. very light west-southwest breeze (near calms) . gull resting on rock in south portion of lake. fishermen out in force today. algal bloom appears to persist.

Rain on 8-19. partly cloudy- south-southeast breeze (no whitecaps) . increasing clouds- rain expected on 8-22. 2 loons north of point- 2 gulls on and near rock- hawk over point. slightly less suspended water particles comparable to 7-26.

Rain on 8-22 and on 8-25. partly cloudy- light (very) variable breeze-north-northeast to sw. slight increase of suspended particles since last. 7 gulls north of island- 8 ducks heading east (low) - bald eagle perched on point in white pine- hawk soaring

Partly sunny- S breeze (no whitecaps) . Sunday of labor day weekend. plenty of floating bits of vegetation from heavy traffic. bald eagle over north end of lake- assorted gulls flying over/bobbing on north half of lake- unseen loon heard.

Partly cloudy- light NNW breeze (no white caps) . rained last on 9-3 and 9-4. algae bloom appears to be over. up to 18 gulls- most bobbing on N portion of lake. 2 bald eagles (1 was juvenile) soaring near southeast portion of lake.

Occasional rain on 9-10 and from 9/12-9/16. sunny light north breeze (no whitecaps) . some decrease of suspended water particles noted. bald eagle over southwest quarter of lake- 3 gulls to north of island- 2 ducks swimming in southwest corn

Rain from 9/20-9/21- from 9/23-9/24. partly sunny- SW breeze (no whitecaps) . increasing clouds from southwest. somewhat less murky than previous sample. 2 gulls bobbing NW of island- 1 gull resting on rock. my older brother Lenny was along today.

Periodic rain from 9/26-9/28 and very early 9/30. partly cloudy (cirrus) - south-southwest breeze (no whitecaps) . murkiness is decreasing. wind speed increased after sampling time. 11 gulls on lake. heron spotted 1/2 mile downstream on pioneer creek.
Rain/sleet mix on 10-2- rain on 10-6. partly cloudy (cirrus) - very light south-southeast breeze. water still somewhat murky. 1 gull perched on rock.

Rain on 10-9- light snow early on 10-10. partly sunny- increasing clouds. NE breeze (no whitecaps) . water only slightly murky-almost clear. 1 gull flying over lake. 1 duck .75 mile downstream on pioneer creek.
Rained early 10-15- from late 10-16 to morning of 10-18. partly cloudy (cirrus) . light south-southeast breeze (no whitecaps) . water is virtually clear- 1 gull bobbing on north end of lake.

Rain from afternoon of 10-21 to morning of 10-24- mist on 10-26. today sunny west-southwest breeze (no whitecaps) . cirrus clouds moving in form the w. rain expected on 10-29. this card marks my last sampling for the 1996 season. see you again in 1997!
Partly sunny- light and variable easterly breeze (no whitecaps) .  Rained late afternoon 6-11- more rain expected later today.

Partly cloudy- SW breeze- no whitecaps.  Cirrus clouds increasing southwest- warm.  Heron seen on pioneer creek- muskrat seen swimming in pioneer creek on my way home.  Water was murky but not overly so.

Partly sunny with increasing cumulus and cirrus clouds.  Light south-southwest breeze- water was murkier than on the 6-27 outing.  Dragonflies kept us company on this outing.  We noted a heron- a family of 8 ducks- and numerous sunning turtles.
Rained on 7-7pm-7-8am-7-13am-7-14am and pm.  Today is partly cloudy with westerly breeze- no whitecaps.  Water not as murky as last- gull- osprey- turtles and duck family.

Rained on 7-16. today is partly sunny- easterly breeze- no whitecaps.  Water was virtually clear.  Two herons seen- one near creek mouth- the other .75 mile downstream.  Hawk- gull- turtles sunning themselves.

Rained on 7-22 pm. and on 7-25. today is partly sunny/cloudy- light NE breeze- no whitecaps.  Water only slightly murky.  Numerous turtles sunning- two gulls bald eagle fishing in lake- immature eagle in flight over lake.

Rained from late pm 7-31 to am 8-1 and on am 8-3.  Today partly cloudy- light northwesterly breeze. cumulus and cirrus clouds increasing.  Water somewhat murkier than last.  Heron- 3 gulls- bald eagle- usual turtles. rain expected later.
Occasional light rain on 8-10 early am. and on 8-12.  Today is partly cloudy- NNW breeze- no whitecaps.  Numerous turtles- 4 gulls- 2 bald eagles.
Rained from 8-14 to 8-15 am- from 8-15 evening to 8-16 early am and on 8-17am.  Today is partly sunny/cloudy- light northwesterly breeze.  8 gulls- ducks- numerous turtles.  16 ducks. algal bloom

Light rain and drizzle from 8-19 evening to 8-21 early AM- and on 8-23 PM.  Today is partly sunny (cirrus clouds) - light south-southeast breeze - algae bloom persists. 6 gulls- 1 loon- bald eagle- turtles.
Rain on 8/25 and 8/30- 9/1- sunny light breeze. birds: herons- 5 gulls- group 12 ducks.  Bloom persists. less turtles then normal.
Rain: September 5- 7 and 9- partly sunny- northern wind- no white caps- 14 ducks on creek- 8 turtles- one heron- 1 loon heard- and many gulls
Rain 9/14-917- sunny- westerly breeze- 4 gulls- 16 ducks- one loon- and one turtle- water was slightly murky
Occasional rain from 9/18-9/20- partly sunny/cloudy- water slightly murky- 2 gulls- 1 duck- 1 bald eagle
Rain last on 9/22- today is partly sunny with south-south east breezy- water slightly murky- clouds are increasing- 2 gulls- 2 ducks on south shore of lake
Rain on 9/27-9/30- today it was sunny- light south-southeast breeze- noted gull on rock and another near sampling site- a duck flew over the creek.
Rain 10/3- 10/6-10/7 and 10/8- partly sunny- southerly breeze- water almost clear- one gull was seen perched on a rock another flying over northern portion of lake.
Sunny with very light northerly breeze- water very clear- rain 10/8-10/9- 10/12-10/13- 10/13 -10/14.

Light rain 10/18 + 10/19- light snow and flurries 10/20-10/22- today partly cloudy- light south-southeast breeze almost calm- water was slightly murky- 2 ducks swimming 2/3 mile down on pioneer creek.
No rain since 10/23- today partly cloudy- breeze west-northwest- 4 gulls and 5 ducks- pioneer creek is beginning to ice over in spots
Partly cloudy light NE breeze.  One loon heard on N end of lake.
Sunny hazy.  Very light south-southwest breeze.  Hawk caught lunch from southern portion of lake. intermittent showers late May.
Partly sunny WNW breeze. unseen loon heard in island area. rainy period 0526-0602.
Partly sunny very light easterly breeze. heron seen east of island. bald eagle flying west from point.  Rain 6/7 and 6/9.
Partly cloudy light northerly breeze. duck family seen along pioneer creek.
Partly sunny with a westerly breeze.  Mother loon NW of the island with one baby on her back.
Partly cloudy south-southwest breeze.  Bald eagle in flight near point.
Partly cloudy light east-northeast breeze.  Bald eagle in flight near island.  Duck family near landing.
Partly sunny light northerly breeze.  Ducks noted along creek loon heard at north end of lake.
Partly cloudy NW breeze.  Loon swimming north of point. numerous gulls noted on lake. seven ducks along creek. rain 7/18 and 7/19.
Partly cloudy low breeze.  Loon and bald eagle noted at north end of lake.  Algae bloom underway. rain 7/3- 7/5- 7/6- 7/7- 7/14- 7/18- 7/19- 7/26- 7/27- 7/28- 7/29.
Partly cloudy light south-southwest breeze.  Bald eagle flying north of point.  Numerous ducks and turtles along creek.  Algae bloom persists.
Partly cloudy hazy. light NW breeze.  Twelve ducks and a few turtles along creek.  Bald eagle flew over creek. rain 8/8 and 8/9.
Partly cloudy light northerly breeze.  Five gulls noted on lake. four ducks noted along creek. rain 8/14 afternoon and evening.
Partly cloudy light wsw breeze. eleven ducks along creek. three loons and eight gulls in N portion of lake. algae bloom persists. rain 8/19 and 8/20.
Partly sunny WNW breeze. eleven ducks in lake near creek mouth.  Two loons seen between sampling site and point.
Sunny very light easterly breeze (almost calm) . four ducks along creek six gulls on lake.  Algae bloom persists.
Partly sunny light northerly breeze.  Flock of 25 geese seen headed south two gulls noted.  Cooler. rain 9/7.
Partly cloudy light wsw breeze.  Two loons noted NW of point.  Eleven gulls noted on lake.  Decreasing clouds.
Partly sunny light westerly breeze.  Bald eagle soaring over point.  Flock of 25 geese headed south.  Six gulls on lake.
Sunny light SW breeze. one loon noted NE of sampling site. two gulls on south lake portion. four ducks along creek. rain 9/25 9/26 9/29/ and 9/30.
Partly cloudy sse breeze. four gulls seen on lake. bald eagle over NW lakeshore. one deer and one turtle along creek.
Partly cloudy SW breeze.  Six gulls noted one loon seen between point and sampling site.
Partly sunny (cirrus clouds) light easterly breeze.  Four gulls noted. one loon was seen west of island.  Another loon was seen north of point.
Partly sunny northerly breeze.  Loon noted in sampling area two gulls noted.  Two ducks flew over southern portion of lake. increasing clouds and cold.
Sunny very light NW breeze.  Six ducks noted in S portion of lake. one gull seen along N lakeshore. two otters or beavers seen swimming in creek.  Weather fairly  mild. rain
Sunny- light N breeze- 4 ducks + 1 turtle along pioneer cr- flying heron headed toward lake.

Partly cloudy- light variable SW breeze. 2 bald eagles soared S of pioneer cr- 2 beaver swimming- 1 in creek- the other in lake. 1 duck flew over lake N of sampling site- buck crossed creek and several turtles noted.  Rained on 5/31- with trace on 6/1.
Partly cloudy- light E breeze.  Loon W of sampling site. 2 ducks and 1 beaver in pioneer cr- rained in a.m. and eve. of 6/5 and 6/6.
Partly sunny- light NW breeze.  Group of 13 ducks swimming in pioneer cr- several rains from 6/8 to 6/11- traces on 6/14 and 6/15 early a.m.- more rain expected.  Very breezy yesterday.
Partly cloudy- light sse breeze. hazy- bald eagle had lunch near W shore- 2 gulls in island area- 3 turtles and 1 duck along pioneer cr.  Rained in afternoon of 6/16 and in a.m. of 6/20.

Partly sunny- WNW breeze- bald eagle soared over S lake area- 11 ducks swimming on a pier along pioneer cr.  Rained on 6/23 and 6/28- with trace on 6/27.  1999 dip in today.  More rain expected tonight.
Partly cloudy- NW breeze- 3 turtles sunning along pioneer cr- mallard swimming in creek- just downstream from lake.  2.21" rain since last outing.
Partly sunny- light W breeze- 2 turtles and 1 duck along pioneer cr- 3.21" rain since 7/7.
Sunny- light N breeze.  Bald eagle flying over point.  Algae bloom beginning   increase in suspended water particles.  0.24" rain since last outing.
Partly sunny- light wsw breeze- warm and humid.  Algae bloom appears to be in progress.  Hawk flying near island- loon swam S of point- 3 ducks noted along pioneer cr- 0.51" rain since 7/17 outing.
Sunny- light wsw breeze- warm- 8 ducks swimming in pioneer cr- just of the lake.  .94" rain since 7/22.
Partly sunny- W breeze- 7 ducks and 3 turtles along pioneer cr- 2 bald eagles flying in island area. 1.22" rain since 7/27 outing.

Partly sunny- light W breeze- gull perched on rock with 3 others flying nearby. mother duck and 2 ducklings- and blue heron along pioneer cr.  Emergent vegetation becoming more prevalent.  0.47" rain since 8/2 outing.
Partly cloudy- very light E breeze- 17 gulls on lake.  Heron along pioneer cr- algae bloom in progress.  2.03" rain since 8/11.
Partly sunny- very light N breeze- humid and hazy.  Algae bloom persists.  7 gulls on N lake area.  0.2" rain since 8/19.

Partly cloudy (cirrus) - S breeze- bald eagle soaring over N lake area- loon bobbing S of sampling site- 4 gulls on lake- with another perched on rock- 4 ducks seen in rock area.  Algol bloom appears to have eased slightly.  No rain since 8/25.
Mostly sunny- sse breeze- 6 gulls and 1 loon noted- 6 ducks flew in island area.  Bald eagle soared over northern lake area.  Rain total since 8/30 outing 0.11".

Partly cloudy + cool. light westerly breeze- 3 gulls noted.  Bald eagle soared over northern lake area.  4 ducks seen along pioneer creek.  Rain total since 9/7 outing 0.74".  Rained last on 9/4 afternoon.  It was windy last 2 days.

Partly sunny- light westerly breeze.  Loon in winter plumage seen south of sampling site.  2 bald eagles soared over pioneer creek.  1 duck seen along creek.  6 gulls noted on lake. rain total since 9/15 outing 0.5".
Sunny- wsw breeze- 15 gulls seen on lake.  Loon noted to the SW of sampling site.  1 duck seen in flight over pioneer creek.  Rain total since 9/21 outing 0.32".
Sunny- light easterly breeze. 5 gulls seen on lake. loon noted to the west of island.  Rain total since 9/30 outing 0.01".
Partly cloudy- light northerly breeze.  3 gulls noted on lake. 2 loons seen between point and island.  A certain amount of suspended particles remain.  Rain total since 10/6 outing: 1.03"
Partly cloudy- light westerly breeze- 3 gulls seen on lake. rain total since 10/11 outing 0.34".

Partly sunny- light westerly breeze- 1 gull seen flying near island- 2 others noted in NW lake area.  Loon seen to the SE of sampling site. 3 ducks seen along pioneer creek.  Rain total since 10/20 outing 0.13".  This was my outing #100.
Partly cloudy- light SW breeze- 7 ducks and 4 turtles noted along pioneer creek.
Partly sunny- WNW breeze- 15 ducks seen resting along pioneer creek and rainfall total since 6/6 outing: 6.56".  Mother nature has been most uncooperative this month!

Partly cloudy- light ese breeze- more suspended particles in water- probably due to increased use- heron seen flying over lake- 10 turtles seen along pioneer creek- and rainfall total since 6/29 outing: 3.41".  Participated in the 2000 secchi dip in!
Partly cloudy- light sse breeze. bald eagle in flight over N end of lake. unseen loon heard. 3 turtles seen along pioneer creek. rainfall since 7/04 - 2.70".

Sunny- very light southerly breeze- hawk lunched for northern lake area- 2 bald eagles seen- one on point white pine- the other on west shore white pine- 1 turtle and 1 beaver seen along pioneer creek- and rainfall total since 7/11 outing: 0.06".
Partly cloudy- light SW breeze- 3 bald eagles and 5 gulls observed while out on this lake outing- 8 ducks and 3 turtles seen along pioneer creek- and rainfall total since 7/19 outing: 0.16".

Partly cloudy- light easterly breeze- warm and humid- algal bloom in progress- bald eagle caught lunch south of point- 10 gulls also seen- 2 ducks and 1 turtle seen along pioneer creek- and rainfall total since 7/24 outing: 1.71".
Partly sunny- light northwesterly breeze- 5 gulls seen on northern lake area- 5 ducks and 1 turtle seen along pioneer creek- algal bloom progressing- and rainfall total since 7/31 outing: 0.97".
Partly cloud- light NNW breeze. 6 gulls seen on lake- 2 eagles and 1 hawk over lake. 1 duck along pioneer creek. algae bloom persists. rainfall since 8/10 = 0.81".
Partly cloudy- very light NW breeze- algal bloom persists- 6 gulls noted on lake- most in northern area- 4 ducks noted along pioneer creek- and rainfall total since 8/16 outing: 0.22".

Sunny- NW breeze- algal bloom continues- 11 gulls noted on lake- loon seen and heard in western lake area- 2 bald eagles searched for lunch over northern lake area- and rainfall total since 8/23 outing: 0.91".
Sunny- light sse breeze- 8 gulls seen on lake- algal bloom coninues- and rainfall total since 8/29 outing: 1.14".
Partly cloudy- very light variable breeze- algal bloom continues. 12 gulls noted on lake- eagle over northern shore. moderate lake use by seaplanes. rainfall total since 9/05 = 0.49".
Partly cloudy- light NW breeze. algal bloom is easing. a pair of loons were noted to SW of sampling site. rainfall since 9/10 = 0.80".
Partly cloudy- cirrus clouds- SW breeze. loon seen to the SW of sampling site. eagle over NE lake area. rainfall since 9/21 = 0.29"

Partly cloudy with cirrus clouds. light westerly breeze. 4 gulls on lake- 2 eagles in flight over NE part of lake. loon in north. clouds increasing with time. water gradually clearing. rainfall since 9/26 = 0.02"
Partly cloudy with cirrus clouds. light NW breeze. eagle- duck and 5 gulls on this outing. precip total since 10/03 = 0.33".
Partly cloudy with cirrus clouds. light NW breeze. 4 gulls and 1 loon seen on this outing.  Rainfall total since 10/09 = 0.43".
Partly cloudy with cirrus clouds. sse breeze. 6 gulls noted. rainfall total since 10/18 = 0.33". this was my 19th outing in 2000- 119 in all. hope to be back next year. (we hope so too- Mr. Posto!).
Full sun.  Light chop to the surface water.  Surface water temp 68*F. Air temp 74*F. Max depth is 30'.

column1: Mature and immature eagles. Loon. Song sparrows. Red-wing Blackbirds.
With Sterling Strathe Full sun. Air temp 74*F. Very slight chop to water surface. Surface temp 70*F.

column2: Beautiful- sunny day. Light wind - 5 MPH. Water temperature 65 degrees. Lake depth 28 feet.
Beautiful- sunny day. Mostly clear sky. Lake depth 28 feet. water temperature 60 degrees.
Sunny day. Humid. Lake depth 28.3 feet. water temperature 67 degrees.
Dam at South Twin- 1 inch. Sunny. Choppy water. Water temperature 48.75 degrees. Lake depth 29 feet.
Dam at south twin 1 inch. Partly sunny. Water temperature 64 degrees. Lake depth 29 feet. Lots of boat traffic.
overcast and breezy. water temperature 63 degrees. Lake depth 28 feet. Dam at one inch.
sunny sky. Very small ripple on water. Water temperature 68 degrees. Lake depth 28 feet.
sunny and windy. No clouds. water temperature 67 degrees. Lake depth 28 feet.
small ripple on water. Sunny. Water temperature 70 degrees. Lake depth 28 feet. Dam at one inch.
small ripple on water. sunny- humid day. Lake depth 28 feet. Water temperature 80 degrees.
sunny and clear. light breeze. water temperature 76 degrees. Lake depth 28 feet. Had two inches rain. Dam open at 6. Lake up 4 inches.
Dam open 7 inches. Lake up 7 inches. Total with rain 11.5 inches. Partly cloudy. Chop on water.
Dam at 6. Clear sky- chop on water. Lake depth 28 feet. Temperature of the water 73 degrees.
Dam at 1. Partly cloudy. Light chop on water. Lake depth 28 feet. Water temperature 70 degrees.
Dam at 1. Beautiful clear sky. water temperature 73 degrees. Lake depth 28 feet.
Dam at 1. Sky mostly clear. Breezy- light chop. Lake depth 28 feet. water temperature 71 degrees.

column1: August 28- 2020 - No secchi reading taken on Friday. Rain. Saturday - lake flooding due to dam. Boat removed. Done for year. Dam setting at 10. Maximum this lake can handle with no rain is 8.

column2: Dam at 4. Sunny- lite chop. Lake depth 29 feet. Water temperature is 63 degrees.
Dam at 1. Sky clear. Lake depth 28.6 feet. Water temperature is 57.75 degrees.
Dam at 9. Cloudy. Choppy water. water temperature 60 degrees. Lake depth 29.5 feet. High water. Dale's dock in under water again. Took his boat out. Flooded again. Soil erosion!!
